&lt;!-- &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; --&gt;
&lt;svg class=&#34;svg-inline--fa fas fa-link anchor&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; role=&#34;img&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 576 512&#34;&gt;&lt;use href=&#34;#fas-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In conclusion, the potential price increase of the Google Pixel lineup is a significant development that could have a major impact on the market. While the devices are known for their high-quality cameras and seamless integration with Google&amp;rsquo;s ecosystem, the price increase could make them less competitive in the market. Consumers who are already hesitant to spend a high amount on a smartphone or smartwatch might be deterred by the increased price point, which could ultimately affect Google&amp;rsquo;s revenue and market share.&lt;/p&gt;
